Given a list of conditions, please answer the question. Condition 1:  The tank being filled is right cylindrical and has circular bases. Condition 2: The volume of water being added to the tank is $20\pi$ cubic meters per hour. Condition 3: As the tank is filled, the water level inside rises by four meters per hour. Condition 4: As shown in the diagram: [asy]import graph;
unitdisk(20);
graph{
cycle(0,0)(0:20)--A--(0,20)--cycle;

unitdisk(-20,-20);
graph{
cycle(0,0)(0:-20)--B--(0,-20)--cycle;

(A--B)--(0,-10);
fill((0,-10)--B--C--cycle,(0,-14)--B--cycle);

label("4", (0,-12), SE);

label("radius"), (-10,20), E);

label("height"), (0,22), N);

};
[/asy], the height of the tank increases by four meters per hour, while its radius remains constant.
Question: What is the value of the radius of the tank, in simplest radical form?

